translated: Jonsson, Sven Olof, hospital physician, Vadstena. Born on July 31, 1898 in Sköllersta, Örebro County. His parents were the principal, Johan Vilhelm J., and Ebba Lovisa Amalia Gripemberg. He married Rosa Fredner in 1927. They had three children: Barbro Gripenberg-J. (born 1928), Kerstin Gripenberg-J. (born 1930), and Anna Lena Gripenberg-J (born 1941). Sven attended Örebro County upper secondary school and received his Bachelor of Medicine degree from Uppsala University in 1923. In 1927, he obtained his license to practice medicine in Stockholm. He worked as an assistant physician at the Örebro County Hospital surgical department from 1925 to 1928 and at its medical department from 1927 to 1928. From 1929 to 1931, he served as the second assistant physician at the surgical department and then as an assistant physician until 1933. Sven was also a temporary second consultant at the Seraf Children's Hospital surgical clinic from 1928 to 1929 and in 1930 and a permanent assistant physician from 1932 to 1933. He worked as an assistant physician at the surgical policlinic from 1931 to 1934 and as a first assistant physician from 1934 to 1935 and as an assistant surgeon from 1935 to 1936. From 1936 to 1937, he worked as an assistant physician at the General Maternity Hospital in Stockholm and as a temporary hospital physician at the Östersund County Hospital surgical department and in Karlshamn in 1937. In 1937 and 1938, he worked at the Ludvika County Hospital. In 1938, he worked as a deputy hospital physician and first assistant physician at the Jönköping County Hospital surgical department. From 1939 to 1946, he worked as a deputy hospital physician and first assistant physician at the Linköping County Hospital surgical department. Sven became the hospital physician at Vadstena County Hospital in 1946.
